title: For Sale/Trade:  1936 German Luger
postcontent: Asking $1800.00 but will consider offers. Many more pictures available if interested. Incredible condition! I believe this gun is UNFIRED!!! I've owned guns for over 55 years and this Luger does not look to me as if it has ever been fired! I am NOT a Luger expert, but this one is exceptional. Look at the pictures closely for signs of wear! I'm not talking about just the blue, look at the parts too! I just don't see any physical wear! All the numbers that I can find are a match! They do not appear to me to be "forced" or redone. The serial number ends with an A.  I bought this Luger in 1994. At the time I vaguely recall the seller saying that the Luger had come from Russia. The collapse of the Soviet Union was in 1991. I believe he told me that the gun had been imported into the USA after that event. I've had questions regarding the grips, the marking on the underside of the barrel. I've also had questions about the number 26 on the left side of the gun which looks etched possibly done with an electric pencil (see picture #2). During a Google search I found a picture of grips identical to the grips on the gun. That picture indicated that they were VOPO Luger grips. I have done additional searches which have led me to believe that the gun is an East German VoPo (Volkspolizei = Peoples Police) Luger. I have taken many different pictures. Some have been cropped to show as much detail as possible. Some of the pictures have had the contrast and or the light adjusted to show more detail. If they shade of blue looks inconsistent in different pictures that would be why. The gun is a very even shade of blue! If there are additional areas you would like to see then please let me know. I will do my best to provide them for you. If you do message me, please include at least your first name and your state. I have set a reasonable reserve just a bit below the Buy It Now I will ship as soon as possible after payment has been received. I will ship through my FFL. Regarding C&R FFL's; it depends on the state and my FFL. If you are a C&R FFL and I can not for some reason ship to you due to your state laws we will work something out. Message me with your name and state. The bottom line with C&R FFL's is that I do not wish to break the law! I will not ship to California, Alaska, or Hawaii You will pay the shipping. If you have questions please ask. One last thing, I am new to Gun Broker and only have 1 feedback. I have however been on Ebay since November of 1998 and currently have 796 positive feedbacks. You can check me out on Ebay under the name Knights42. In some cases I might take PayPal, but we should correspond about that prior to your bidding. Let me close by saying that this is an exceptional Luger and I believe you will be very happy if you are the next owner!!! Thank you for looking.
